headline: These Stocks Moved the Most Today: Tesla, Cleveland-Cliffs, Quantum Computing, Oklo, SailPoint, Lockheed, and More
summary: Stocks wavered on Wednesday as Wall Street took stock of the trade deal with China that President Donald Trump described as “done.” It leaves a 55% tariff on goods imported from China.  Tesla  was up slightly, bringing its winning streak to four sessions.  Shares of the maker of electric vehicles jumped 5.7% in the previous session after a video revealed a driverless Tesla vehicle on the streets of Austin, Texas.
